  "texts": [
    "• \"financial dominance\" if the central bank official:",
    "-suggests that the central bank should support the financial markets (e.g., provide liquidity support, recapitalize or bail out banks) regardless of inflation -suggests not to tighten the monetary policy stance (e.g.",
    "not to raise interest rates) if this threatens financial stability -suggests that financial market stress is making monetary policy more difficult -is concerned about negative feedback effects from the financial markets (e.g.",
    "doom loop, contagion) -suggests that the central bank will inject liquidity via non-bank financial intermediaries or repo markets, will bail out or recapitalise banks • \"fiscal dominance\" if the central bank official:",
    "-is accommodating to government policies (e.g., suggests to bring down sovereign bond spreads to help reach sustainable growth)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}